{"document_id": "9a7013a761314576999588794d2811cd__0", "text": "--- session ---\nAppt APT-2024-08-15-001 Portal https://tele.example.in/visit\nClient IP 103.21.244.12 Device IMEI 356938035643809\nMAC 00:1A:2B:3C:4D:5E\n--- chat ---\nPatient Sweta Naik 21 Female (9876543210, sweta.naik@example.com): Hello doctor, I'm feeling very anxious lately. My heart races and I feel shaky.\nDr Dr. Anjali Sharma (Goa Medical College & Hospital): Hello Sweta, I understand this is distressing. Can you tell me more about when these episodes of anxiety occur?\nPatient Sweta Naik: It happens mostly in the mornings before I start my day. I worry about everything, even small things. I feel like I can't control my thoughts.\nDr Dr. Anjali Sharma: It sounds like generalized anxiety. We can discuss some coping strategies. Have you experienced any panic attacks, where you feel you might lose control or faint?\nPatient Sweta Naik: Yes, once or twice. I was at the market and suddenly felt like I couldn't breathe. I had to sit down. It was very scary.\nDr Dr. Anjali Sharma: I see. Given your symptoms, I recommend starting a low-dose SSRI medication and scheduling a follow-up in two weeks. I will send the prescription to your registered email.\nPatient Sweta Naik: Okay, thank you. What about the side effects? I am worried about gaining weight.\nDr Dr. Anjali Sharma: Weight gain is a possible side effect, but not everyone experiences it. We will monitor you closely. For now, try deep breathing exercises when you feel anxious.\nPatient Sweta Naik: I will try. Thank you for your help, doctor.\nDr Dr. Anjali Sharma: You are welcome, Sweta. Please don't hesitate to reach out if you need anything before our next appointment. Take care.", "tokenized_text": ["-", "-", "-", "session", "-", "-", "-", "Appt", "APT", "-", "2024", "-", "08", "-", "15", "-", "001", "Portal", "https", ":", "/", "/", "tele", ".", "example", ".", "in", "/", "visit", "Client", "IP", "103.21.244.12", "Device", "IMEI", "3569380356